deck: Leader of the Smashers.
description: Mr. Bowers or Mastermind as he was dubbed by Iron Man was the leader of a group of thugs he called the Smashers. Mr. Bowers was an employee of a Stark Factory on Lakani island. He had been embezzling money from the plant for some time before he created the Smashers. The Smashers were put together to cause as much of a ruckus as they could so that the factory would get shut down which in turn would hide Bowers embezzlement. Bowers and his group were stopped easily enough by Iron Man.
name: Mastermind

deck: Citizen of Lakani Island.
description: Kathy Ffoulkes along with her father Hubert set up a peaceful protest to have a Stark factory on the island of Lakani shut down. They feared that the factory would end up polluting the entire island. A lot of their fears however were false information that was spread through the Smashers. The Smashers being a group of paid thugs working for a man Iron Man dubbed Mastermind. The group was eventually defeated by Iron Man and it was discovered that Mastermind was actually a Mr. Bowers a Stark employee who was embezzling from the company and hoped to get the factory shut down in order to hide his crimes.
name: Kathy Ffoulkes

deck: Major of Lakani Island.
description: Major Hubert Ffoulkes and his daughter Kathy were the prime antagonist against Tony Stark having a factory on the island of Lakani. Hubert believed that people should live a more simple life and that machines only caused pollution and made the land unlivable. Although he led a peaceful protest a group known as the Smashers had a more violent method for shutting down the Stark plant. Iron Man however was able to take down the group and their leader Mastermind who was in actuality a Mr. Bowers an employee of Stark's that had been embezzling money. Bowers had hoped to cause as much of a ruckus as he could to shut down the plant in order to hide his crimes.
name: Hubert Ffoulkes

deck: A young woman murdered by the Pride.
description:
Destiny Gonzales was a young runaway that was abducted by an evil organization called the Pride. The Pride used Destiny in a sacrificial ritual, but unbeknownst to the Pride their children who had no idea what their parents were up to had witnessed the entire ordeal through a 2 way mirror.

Those same children then attempted to phone the police and confess to them what had occurred and that their parents were secretly super villains but they weren't taken seriously and decided to gather more evidence before going to the police again.

Later the Pride found out what the kids had been up to so they framed them all for the murder of Destiny in order to stop them from going to the police and as they were now wanted fugitives.
name: Destiny Gonzales

deck: A girl from the human colony world of Vulcrugon who became embroiled in an interstellar war.
description:
Origin

Ardeni was drawn into a war between humanity and the alien Juglar Empire after the Jugla's discovered a latent psychic power in her and her twin brother Arlen. The Jugla's brought out this latent ability, planning to use the siblings as pawns to destroy Earth.

Ardeni managed to break free of the Jugla mind control at the last minute before Earth's Sun was to be destroyed and was forced to kill her brother, she was then able to use her abilities to repair the sun.

Creation

Ardeni was created by Alan Hebden and Jesus Redondo for the anthology comic Starlord. The strip ran from the second issue all the way till the comic was cancelled and merged with 2000AD.

Major Story Arcs

After the death of her brother, Ardeni vowed to find the Juglar home world and destroy it herself, she traveled the galaxy searching for it, eventually finding an ancient power named The Green Star.

The Green Star and Ardeni communicated with each other for some time, and she learned the location of the Juglar home world. However Ardeni's experience with the Green Star profoundly changed her, and after finally reaching her destination she decided to simply make all of humanity and the Juglar's weaponry inoperable for good, thereby ending the war with no bloodshed.
name: Ardeni Lakam

deck: Nigerian superhero.
description:
Powerman is a Nigerian hero with superhuman strength and durability. His only vulnerability is to snake bites; if he is bitten, he can recover by electrocuting himself.

NB: For reprints in the USA, he was renamed Powerbolt, to avoid potential confusion with Marvel's Luke Cage. The character was produced on behalf of a Nigerian company, Picin, and published there, but the creative team were British, as Picin felt there was at the time a lack of home grown talent available.
name: Powerman
